Swiss Held New U.S. Talks on Client Data, SonntagsZeitung Says

-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 
2011-04-17T11:12:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/actelion-isn-t-concerned-about-audit-sonntagszeitung-reports.html
Michael Ambuehl, Switzerland’s
state secretary to the  finance ministry , and Finance Minister
Eveline Widmer-Schlumpf discussed supplying new information on
holders of Swiss bank accounts to other countries,
 SonntagsZeitung  reported, citing a spokesman for Ambuehl.  “No details of the meeting will be disclosed,” the
spokesman, Mario Tuor, told the newspaper after discussions last
week in  Washington . The deal affects clients of about 24 Swiss
banks that used foundations set up in Liechtenstein, the
SonntagsZeitung reported, citing an “insider” it didn’t name.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Zurich at 
 gbroom@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net . 